remonstrate - the CPP-style SCOLD preprocesor

Outreach
   http://www.scold-lang.org
   git://git.scold-lang.org

The current preprocessor

usage:
    remonstrate [ options ] ... files.xcpp ...

options :=

   --srcdir=<scold-source-directory>               (input)

   --modulesdir=DIRECTORY                               same as --modulesdir-directory
   --modulesdir-directory=<c++-declarations-directory>  [output] declarations directory
   --modulesdir-variable='$(VARIABLE)'                  defaults to '$(modulesdir)'
     maybe you want '$(scold_modulesdir)' for baleful-ballad in hypogeal-twilight

   --objdir=DIRECTORY                                   same as --objdir-directory
   --objdir-directory=<c++-objects-directory>           definitions directory
   --objdir-variable='$(VARIABLE)'                      defaults to '$(objdir)'
     maybe you want '$(scold_cxx_objdir)' for baleful-ballad in hypogeal-twilight

   [ -Idirectory                       include file to find other modules
     --include=directory ]
   [ -Erootdir                         external (sub-)modules with
     --external=rootdir                    .../obj/modules, .../obj/src, .../src
     --submodule=rootdir ]

   [ --insert-namespace                insert enclosing namespace (or not)
     --no-insert-namespace ]           default: on
   [ --matryoshka-namespace-nesting    insert enclosing namespace (or not)
     --no-insert-namespace ]           default: off

   [ --help | --usage ]                emit this
   [ --version ]                       emit the version, exit
   [ --verbose ]                       prattle
   [ --quiet ]                         shut. up.
   [ --dry-run ]                       show what might be done


The file.xcpp are each burst up into the five phases of C++ declaration-to-definition
according to the "#divert" syntax of the XML-style scaffolding.

file.xcpp
    #divert <fpp>
    ...forward declarations...
    #divert </fpp>
    #divert <hpp>
    ...complete "header" declarations...
    #divert </hpp>
    #divert <ipp>
    ...inline definitions...
    #divert </ipp>
    #divert <tpp>
    ...outline template function definition declarations...
    #divert </tpp>
    #divert <cpp>
    ...outline definitions...
    #divert </cpp>

The corresponding C++ modules are created in ${objdir}/modules.  The modules are
referenced from within the *.xcpp overlay syntax with an #import directive

    #import std.vector
    #import std.basic_string
    #import my.Class



